# Add Rooms, Auth, Chat History, Friends & Call Logs with PostgreSQL + Prisma

The existing app is a distributed WebSocket chat with Redis pub/sub, Caddy reverse proxy, and WebRTC video calling. All state is ephemeral. This plan adds persistent storage (PostgreSQL + Prisma), user authentication, a room system, 1:1 DM chat, chat history, friend lists, and call logs.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **pgAdmin Setup**: You'll connect pgAdmin to the PostgreSQL container. After `docker compose up`, add a new server in pgAdmin:
> - **Host**: `localhost` | **Port**: `5432` | **Username**: `chatuser` | **Password**: `chatpass` | **DB**: `chatdb`

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking change**: The old "enter a username and connect" login is replaced with proper signup/login. Existing client code will be significantly reworked.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Database & Docker Infrastructure

#### [MODIFY] [docker-compose.yml](file:///Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main%202/Real_Time_Chat_App-main/docker-compose.yml)
- Add a `postgres` service with env vars `POSTGRES_USER=chatuser`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD=chatpass`, `POSTGRES_DB=chatdb`, port `5432:5432`, and a named volume `pg_data`
- Add `DATABASE_URL` env var to all `ws*` services pointing to `postgresql://chatuser:chatpass@postgres:5432/chatdb`
- Add `postgres` to `depends_on` for `ws*` services

---

### Prisma ORM Schema

#### [NEW] [schema.prisma](file:///Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main%202/Real_Time_Chat_App-main/server/prisma/schema.prisma)

```prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

model User {
  id           String        @id @default(uuid())
  username     String        @unique
  email        String        @unique
  passwordHash String
  avatarUrl    String?
  createdAt    DateTime      @default(now())

  sentMessages     Message[]     @relation("sender")
  roomMemberships  RoomMember[]
  sentRequests     Friendship[]  @relation("requester")
  receivedRequests Friendship[]  @relation("addressee")
  callerLogs       CallLog[]    @relation("caller")
  calleeLogs       CallLog[]    @relation("callee")
}

model Room {
  id        String       @id @default(uuid())
  name      String
  isGroup   Boolean      @default(true)  // false = DM
  createdAt DateTime     @default(now())

  members   RoomMember[]
  messages  Message[]
}

model RoomMember {
  id       String   @id @default(uuid())
  userId   String
  roomId   String
  joinedAt DateTime @default(now())

  user User @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  room Room @relation(fields: [roomId], references: [id])

  @@unique([userId, roomId])
}

model Message {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  content   String
  senderId  String
  roomId    String
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())

  sender User @relation("sender", fields: [senderId], references: [id])
  room   Room @relation(fields: [roomId], references: [id])

  @@index([roomId, createdAt])
}

model Friendship {
  id          String           @id @default(uuid())
  requesterId String
  addresseeId String
  status      FriendshipStatus @default(PENDING)
  createdAt   DateTime         @default(now())

  requester User @relation("requester", fields: [requesterId], references: [id])
  addressee User @relation("addressee", fields: [addresseeId], references: [id])

  @@unique([requesterId, addresseeId])
}

enum FriendshipStatus {
  PENDING
  ACCEPTED
  REJECTED
}

model CallLog {
  id         String   @id @default(uuid())
  callerId   String
  calleeId   String
  startedAt  DateTime @default(now())
  endedAt    DateTime?
  duration   Int?     // seconds
  status     String   // "completed", "missed", "rejected"

  caller User @relation("caller", fields: [callerId], references: [id])
  callee User @relation("callee", fields: [calleeId], references: [id])

  @@index([callerId])
  @@index([calleeId])
}
```

