## pgAdmin Setup Instructions

After running `docker compose up`:
1. Open pgAdmin → **Add New Server**
2. **General tab**: Name = `ChatApp`
3. **Connection tab**: Host = `localhost`, Port = `5432`, Username = `chatuser`, Password = `chatpass`
4. Browse to `chatdb` → **Schemas** → **Tables** to see: [User](file:///Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main%202/Real_Time_Chat_App-main/server/src/types.ts#104-105), `Room`, `RoomMember`, [Message](file:///Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main%202/Real_Time_Chat_App-main/client/index.js#116-133), `Friendship`, `CallLog`

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated (Docker)
```bash
cd "/Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main 2/Real_Time_Chat_App-main"
docker compose up --build
```
All services (redis, postgres, ws1, ws2, ws3, caddy) should start healthy.

### Manual Testing (Browser at http://localhost:3000)
1. **Signup**: Create 2 users (UserA, UserB) via signup form
2. **Login**: Login as UserA
3. **Create Room**: Click "Create Room", name it "Test Room", note the Room ID
4. **Join Room**: Login as UserB in another browser/incognito, paste Room ID to join
5. **Group Chat**: Send messages in both browsers — verify real-time delivery and history persistence
6. **DM**: UserA clicks UserB in the user list → sends a DM → verify it appears only for UserB
7. **Chat History**: Refresh page, re-enter room → previous messages load from DB
8. **Friends**: UserA sends friend request to UserB → UserB accepts → both see each other in Friends list
9. **Video Call**: UserA calls UserB → accept → verify WebRTC works → end call
10. **Call Logs**: Check call history tab shows the completed call
11. **pgAdmin**: Connect to DB and verify data in [User](file:///Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main%202/Real_Time_Chat_App-main/server/src/types.ts#104-105), [Message](file:///Users/taranjain/Downloads/Real_Time_Chat_App-main%202/Real_Time_Chat_App-main/client/index.js#116-133), `Room`, `Friendship`, `CallLog` tables
